24/05/2009
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The opposition Order, Law, Justice Party leader Yane Yanev accused the ruling Bulgarian Socialist Party (BSP) on Saturday (May 23rd) of arranging with the country's Roma leaders to secure votes in the July parliamentary elections, media reported. Yanev claimed that 40% of the BSP votes will come from the Roma minority. He said he intends to notify the European Commission of the alleged corruption scheme. (Sofia news agency, Darik, BGNES, Mediapool, Focus - 23/05/09) 
